### Explanation of the Proof

1. **`h₆`**: We prove that `{x | p x ∧ q x}` is in `𝓝 x` by showing that it is the intersection of `{x | p x}` and `{x | q x}`, which are both in `𝓝 x`. This follows directly from the property that the intersection of two neighborhoods is a neighborhood.

